dcterms:description: The Segment Anything Model (SAM) Dataset is a large-scale dataset used for training the SAM model, which enables automated object segmentation without additional training.
dcterms:title: Segment Anything Model (SAM) Dataset

dcterms:description: Images from an F1 mapping population derived from crossing Cabernet Sauvignon and Riesling, used to test the SAM model for berry segmentation.
dcterms:title: F1 mapping population images (Cabernet Sauvignon and Riesling)

dcterms:description: Cluster images with individual berries detached and placed on a white surface, used to validate the SAM algorithm.
dcterms:title: Cluster images with individual berries detached

dcterms:description: Empirical cumulative distribution functions for clusters, used to analyze the spatial distribution of berries within grape clusters.
dcterms:title: Empirical cumulative distribution functions for clusters

dcterms:description: Masks generated by SAM for berry objects, used to analyze berry characteristics and cluster architecture.
dcterms:title: Masks generated by SAM for berry objects
